4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE MONTANA MUSEUMS ACT OF 2020; REVISING
5 THE CRITERIA USED TO MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS FOR GRANTS AWARDED UNDER THE HISTORIC
6 PRESERVATION GRANT PROGRAM; AND AMENDING SECTION 22-3-1306, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 22-3-1306, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "22-3-1306. Priorities for funding -- rulemaking. (1) The department of commerce shall make
12 recommendations for grants awarded under the historic preservation grant program to eligible entities for the
13 preservation of historic sites, historical societies, or history museums in the state.
14 (2) Projects funded under this section must provide that a significant portion of the facility be open
15 to public access and use. Projects that confer only a private a limited public benefit are not eligible.
16 (3) The recommendations must be based on competitive criteria created by the department, as
17 guided by the legislature. The criteria may include:
18 (a) the degree to which the project will protect:
19 (i) the building envelope, consisting of the structure's walls, roof, doors and windows, and
20 foundation; and
21 (ii) its internal utility systems, including electricity, plumbing, and heat;
22 (b) the degree of economic stimulus or economic activity, including job creation and work creation
23 for Montana contractors and service workers;
24 (b) (c) the purpose of the project, including whether it provides features that establish or enhance
25 security, climate control, or fire protection for museums or address infrastructure, maintenance, or building code
26 issues at historic sites;
27 (c) (d) the timing of the project, including access to matching funds, if needed, and approval of permits
28 so that work can be completed without delay;
